title: Album Page, "Town and Château at Coucy", June 1, 1887
medium: Graphite on off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner: (written perpendicular to drawing) 11; at bottom right corner: 11 / 12; bottom right edge of drawing: Town and Chateau at Coucy / June 1st 1887 / from the petit chateau.
description: Horizontal sheet tipped vertically into binding.  Seen from a distance is a large tower in the center of a low, forested and built landscape of small buildings.  The tower is round with an arcaded uppermost story.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "Town and Château at Coucy", June 1, 1887.
June 1, 1887. Graphite on off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-185.
